"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-01-Olympics-Day-5-Gold-rush-for-China-in-diving-swimming-and-BMX-1vHJ9hdO2uk-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Ahmed Ghoneim  Copied  The fifth day of the Paris Olympics saw Yuxi Chen and Hongchan Quan winning gold in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s synchronized diving 10-meter platform, beating the Democratic People\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Republic of North Korea\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s duet of Jin Mi Jo and Mi Rae Kim who came second, leaving Great Britain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Toulson Lois and Andrea Spendolini with the bronze.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Yawen Deng also won the gold in the women's BMX freestyle beating Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Perris Benegas and Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Natalya Diehm.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Boheng Zhang also won silver in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s all-around gymnastics final alongside his teammate Ruoteng Xiao who won bronze, leaving Japan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Shinnosuke Oka to go home with the gold.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s star swimmer Zhanle Pan won the gold in legendary fashion by breaking his world record for the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100-meter swimming freestyle with a time of 46.40. Pan had set the previous world record time at 46.80 earlier this year on February 10 in the World Aquatic Championships in Qatar\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s capital Doha.  China is now in first place in the current Olympic medal rankings at the end of day five with 9 gold medals leaving hosts France in second and Japan in third place.  Team USA also had a good day at the office, with a surprise victory at the quarter-finals of the men's tennis doubles, as Austin Kracjicek and Rajeev Ram beat Spain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s tennis icon Rafael Nadal who had partnered up with the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s number one Carlos Alcaraz. They will now progress to the semi-finals.  The much-awaited basketball game between Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s star-stacked squad against exciting newcomers South Sudan, saw Lebron James lead his country to another emphatic win 103-86, progressing to the quarter-finals. The U.S. will be looking for a historic fifth straight gold medal in men's basketball.  American swimmer Katie Ledecky broke the Olympic record that she set in the 2021 Tokyo Olympics, and won a mind-boggling 12th career Olympic medal, after finishing first in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 1500-meter freestyle final. Ledecky has now tied\\u00a0 Jenny Thompson, Dara Torres, and Natalie Coughlin for the most ever medals won by an American female swimmer.  Hosts France also had a gold medal to celebrate after swimmer Leon Marchand won the Men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 200-meter breaststroke final setting a new Olympic record. Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Zac Stubblety-Cook won the silver and the Netherlands\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Casper Corbeau came in third for the bronze.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"